Barcelona’s prime years are widely considered to be between 2008 and 2012, under Pep Guardiola, when the club dominated both Spanish and European football.

During this era, Barcelona showcased their famous tiki-taka style, built around short passing, possession, and fluid movement. The team, led by stars like Lionel Messi, Xavi, and Andrés Iniesta, won nearly every major trophy available. 

